==English==
===Etymology===
From the early 20th century, when an [[officer]] would threaten to [[draw]] his sabre.

===Noun===
'''[[sabre]]-[[rattling]]''' {{uncountable}}

#{{idiom}} A [[flamboyant]] [[display]] of [[military]] [[power]] as an [[implied]] [[threat]] that it might be used.

